Method behavioural requirements:
- If the string parameter `s` represents an odd number, the integer result is the number of steps required to reduce it to 1 by adding 1 when the number is odd and dividing by 2 when the number is even.
- If the string parameter `s` represents an even number, the integer result is the number of steps required to reduce it to 1 by dividing by 2 when the number is even.